To add a new queue for hostname "foo":

$ mkdir queue/foo

Assuming you're in the top level autotest dir (eg /usr/local/autotest).

-----------------------------------------------------

To add a new queue called "mygroup" for hostnames "foo", "bar", and "blat".

$ mkdir queue/mygroup
$ cat > queue/mygroup/.machines
foo
bar
blat

(Hit ^D after you've typed blat and hit return)
